      "description": "<b>Sauron</b><sprite name=\"commander\"><sprite name=\"emmissary\"><sprite name=\"mage\"><br>Starts with:<br>- Barad-dur <sprite name=\"pc\"/>[1] <sprite name=\"fort\"/>[1]<br>- Mouth of Sauron <sprite name=\"emmissary\"/><br>- Gollum <sprite name=\"agent\"/><br>- A low-quality <mark=#ffff00>Average</mark> <sprite name=\"darkServants\"/>army<br>- Spells <sprite name=\"spell\"/> and Artifacts <sprite name=\"artifact\"/><br><br><b>Difficulty: <mark=#00ff00>Easy</mark></b><br>- Starting Power: <mark=#ffff00>Average</mark><br>- Recruitable characters: <mark=#00ff00>Good</mark><br>- Recruitable armies: <mark=#00ff00>Good</mark><br>- Gameplay style: conquest",
      "joinedTitle": "Ssshire...Bagginz...",
      "joinedText": "Listen well, creature.<br><br>You think your trembling bought you mercy.<br><br>It did not. I kept you because you knew something.<br><br>A place. A name. A direction that others have failed to see.<br><br>A land of small folk and smaller courage.<br><br>A place so insignificant no map dares to mark it.<br><br>Now I know enough. You may scurry back to your holes and rivers. My servants are already on the road.<br><br>The Ring is there — I taste its shadow.<br><br>You are still bound to it, wretch. You will follow it, and I will find you.<br><br>Any creature that finds it will succumb to the Lord of the Rings.",
